Dean Kelley, the National Council of Churches' counselor on religious liberty, wrote a critique of Clarence Thomas that was used as grounds for his organization's opposition to the Supreme Court nominee. Clarence's lack of a sense of community makes his nomination troubling. ; Conservative viewpoint; Virginia Thomas has represented the conservative viewpoint in her jobs as a staffer for a Republican congressman, spokeswoman at the US Chamber of Congress and deputy assistant secretary at the Department of Labor. Some religious rights groups are troubled by her anti-cult activities in light of her former involvement with Lifespring, a motivational group. 